      {
        "content": "# My Game Story: Reflections on Design and Storytelling\n\n**The MIT Press** is a mission-driven, not-for-profit scholarly publisher. Your support helps make it possible for us to create open publishing models and produce books of superior design quality.\n\n[Donate](https://giving.mit.edu/form?fundId=3876985)\n\n[![](https://thereader.mitpress.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/monster-slaying-final-170x110.jpg)](https://thereader.mitpress.mit.edu/the-strange-melancholy-of-slaying-monsters/)\n\n[Media](https://thereader.mitpress.mit.edu/media/)\n\n[",
        "title": "My Game Story: Reflections on Design and Storytelling - Part 10/12",
        "timestamp": "2026-05-23T21:18:48.000Z",
