      {
        "content": "The page excerpt also includes the MIT Press Reader house blurb, describing the publication as illuminating bold ideas and voices from the MIT Press catalog. It says the site publishes thought-provoking excerpts, interviews, and original essays for a general reader while remaining backed by academic rigor. This reinforces the editorial identity of the Reader as a bridge between scholarly work and accessible public writing.",
